aws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084350/2022-trek-roscoe-hardtail-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084350/2022-trek-roscoe-hardtail-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084350/2022-trek-roscoe-hardtail-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084350/2022-trek-roscoe-hardtail-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084350/2022-trek-roscoe-hardtail-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266743\">The 2022 Trek Roscoe frame has two water bottle mounting positions; one on the seat tube and one on the top of the downtube</figcaption></figure><p>As mountain bikes go, hardtails are definitely the easiest to live with, with few moving parts that require constant tender loving care. Trek have made a few important changes to the 2022 Trek Roscoe to make this hardtail even easier to maintain.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek roscoe drops the knock block headset\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084403/2022-trek-roscoe-headset-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>First up, Knock Block is no more. The previous Roscoe required Trek’s proprietary Knock Block headset that prevented the fork crown coming into contact with the side of the downtube; an important feature for preventing these parts from smashing into one another during a crash. From my own experience on a Trek Slash, I can tell you that the blocking functionality of the headset was easily sheared off during a crash. Fortunately, the 2022 Roscoe doesn’t need it, as the fork crown clears the downtube on full rotation of the bars.</p><p>Next, the Roscoe gets a SRAM UDH hanger, meaning you’ll be able to replace a bent hanger very easily, picking it up from almost any bike shop, not just those that are Trek dealers.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek roscoe downtube protection\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084344/2022-trek-roscoe-dual-density-downtube-protector-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Trek have added an internal cable fastener on the downtube. Cables aren’t fully guided internally, so may have had a tendency to rattle about within the aluminium frame, causing unwanted noise. The cable fastener secures the cables to the inside of the downtube, about half way along it, in an attempt to keep noise to a minimum.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek roscoe 9 top chain guide iscg 05 tabs\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28084338/2022-trek-roscoe-9-ethirteen-chain-ring-top-guide-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The Roscoe still runs a 73mm threaded bottom bracket that can take a 30mm spindle. The downtube gets dual-density rubber protection to save the frame from rock strikes, while the chainstay gets a double-sided guard to protect against chain slap. Trek have added an ISCG 05 tab for the mounting of a chain guide and bash guard; the top end Roscoe 9 comes with a top guide.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Though you’ll see four models of the 2022 Trek Roscoe for sale, only the Roscoe 7, Roscoe 8 and Roscoe 9 models get this latest geometry and travel update discussed here. The budget option Roscoe 6, retailing at $1,149.99 USD, is a carry over frame from 2021, so still has the ~67.3° head tube angle, 27.5″+ wheels and 120mm travel fork. It runs an SR Suntour XCM 32mm stanchion coil fork, Alex MD35 Rims, a Shimano Deore 10 speed drivetrain, Shimano MT200 2-piston brakes and an aluminium Bontrager finishing kit.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek roscoe 7\" width=\"1200\" height=\"650\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint-297x161.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint-800x433.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/28091419/2022-trek-roscoe-7-aqua-splatter-fade-paint-120x65.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/e